# selecting the most important currencies

df = data[['Date','CNY=X','INR=X','JPY=X']].set_index('Date')

# Forward fill missing values

df = df.fillna(method='ffill')

# Calculate the percentage change year over year for each currency

pct_change_df = df.pct_change(freq='Y')

In [12]:
# Calculate percentage changes over the past decade

start_date = pd.to_datetime('2013-05-03')
end_date = pd.to_datetime('2023-05-03')
past_decade = (df.index >= start_date) & (df.index <= end_date)
percentage_changes = df.loc[past_decade].pct_change().mean()
In [15]:
# Create bar plot using seaborn

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.barplot(x=percentage_changes.index, y=percentage_changes.values)
plt.title("Average Percentage Change Against USD Over the Past Decade")
plt.ylabel("Percentage Change")
plt.xlabel("Currency")
plt.savefig("AveragePercentage.png")
